The paper proposes a deep learning model to predict packet loss patterns in real-time video streaming scenarios. This involves analyzing time-series data and making predictions based on patterns. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia), which deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia data. The paper also involves computer vision techniques, as it deals with video streaming, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory, as it deals with data transmission and loss, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category. The paper also involves network infrastructure, as it deals with real-time video streaming, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves deep learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category.
